much people. And the disciples were called Christians first in Antioch.","year":43},{"id":"rec6Oh9SDKcuWIt1o","ref":"Acts.11.27","text":"And in these days came prophets from Jerusalem unto Antioch.","year":43},{"id":"recv9Fwc46xLmKlb6","ref":"Acts.13.1","text":"Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets and teachers; as Barnabas, and Simeon that was called Niger, and Lucius of Cyrene, and Manaen, which had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.","year":45},{"id":"recR3ReTegXlDVw54","ref":"Acts.14.26","text":"And thence sailed to Antioch, from whence they had been recommended to the grace of God for the work which they fulfilled.","year":46}]}
